Cf. OFCCP 

v. 

National City Bank of Cleveland.

 30 Fair Empl. Prac. Cas. [BNA] 6, 9 (Sec'y Final Dec. and Order Sept. 9, 1982) (OFCCP vindicates government interest
in terms of contract but does not represent individual complainants or class members). In any event, there is no basis
for concluding that the Compliance Manual confers rights upon a Section 503 defendant which could be raised as defense
to a Section 503 complaint.

Commonwealth also alleges that it was never advised that the conciliation process had reached an impasse except with
respect to Complainant Gray and further that OFCCP never explained how the rejection for employment of Complainants
Etnire, Marshall, Matthis, Sherrard and Zellers violated Section 503. 

